1
00:00:17,220 --> 00:00:18,420
His spirit is completely destroyed.

2
00:00:20,060 --> 00:00:21,180
Nothing can save him now.

3
00:00:21,740 --> 00:00:22,260
Yuxun,

4
00:00:22,860 --> 00:00:24,220
please think of a way to save him.

5
00:00:24,620 --> 00:00:25,740
We can't save him.

6
00:00:26,460 --> 00:00:27,380
Just give up.

7
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:54,860
Why are you doing this?

8
00:00:55,420 --> 00:00:56,860
You'll get yourself killed.

9
00:01:00,020 --> 00:01:01,580
I have to save him.

10
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:06,800
[Immortal Beyond Dust]
[Episode 3]

11
00:01:22,420 --> 00:01:24,100
You're a demon, and he's an immortal.

12
00:01:24,420 --> 00:01:25,620
Your powers are incompatible.

13
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:27,060
You know what to do?

14
00:01:27,460 --> 00:01:28,060
Let me go.

15
00:01:28,620 --> 00:01:30,740
Maybe I can give it a try.

16
00:01:38,060 --> 00:01:39,940
Let me see what I can do.

17
00:01:50,940 --> 00:01:52,100
His immortal soul is damaged.

18
00:01:52,380 --> 00:01:53,860
Only immortal arts can save him.

19
00:01:58,700 --> 00:01:59,820
I still have this.

20
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:02,020
This is just herbs for external wounds.

21
00:02:02,220 --> 00:02:03,540
But his injuries are inside.

22
00:02:06,580 --> 00:02:07,940
Then what do we do?

23
00:02:13,340 --> 00:02:14,580
Don't look at me.

24
00:02:14,900 --> 00:02:16,340
I don't know any immortal arts.

25
00:02:16,740 --> 00:02:18,100
I can't save him.

26
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:24,740
What do we do?

27
00:03:32,860 --> 00:03:34,020
You're awake.

28
00:03:36,780 --> 00:03:37,380
Thank goodness.

29
00:03:38,180 --> 00:03:39,340
You're finally awake.

30
00:03:40,780 --> 00:03:41,780
I'm alright.

31
00:03:43,420 --> 00:03:44,220
Don't cry.

32
00:03:56,940 --> 00:03:57,740
Young Lord,

33
00:03:58,020 --> 00:03:59,260
she refuses to eat anything.

34
00:04:00,020 --> 00:04:01,020
I know.

35
00:04:12,220 --> 00:04:13,980
Why did you meddle and save me?

36
00:04:20,140 --> 00:04:21,180
What are you doing?

37
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:30,660
Eat this, and I'll tell you.

38
00:04:34,420 --> 00:04:35,220
It's not poisoned.

39
00:04:57,300 --> 00:04:58,460
You still haven't answered me.

40
00:04:59,540 --> 00:05:00,740
I don't like owing people.

41
00:05:02,340 --> 00:05:03,420
What do you mean?

42
00:05:24,940 --> 00:05:26,180
How could you be so foolish?

43
00:05:27,140 --> 00:05:28,340
Don't you know

44
00:05:28,780 --> 00:05:30,500
I've been using you?

45
00:05:31,180 --> 00:05:31,940
I know.

46
00:05:32,940 --> 00:05:34,300
I've always known.

47
00:05:35,540 --> 00:05:37,100
But I still had to save you.

48
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:50,500
Don't worry.

49
00:05:51,460 --> 00:05:52,300
With me here,

50
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:54,500
you won't die for now.

51
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:57,100
Did we

52
00:05:58,620 --> 00:05:59,660
know each other?

53
00:06:50,020 --> 00:06:51,500
What a beautiful starry sky.

54
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:55,260
You said

55
00:06:55,260 --> 00:06:56,580
this is the immortal realm?

56
00:06:57,020 --> 00:06:59,180
So if I want to see it,

57
00:06:59,540 --> 00:07:00,660
can I see a sky like this

58
00:07:00,660 --> 00:07:01,580
every day?

59
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:16,900
Another pair of star-crossed lovers.

60
00:07:17,460 --> 00:07:18,180
What a shame.

61
00:07:23,940 --> 00:07:24,740
What are you laughing at?

62
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:28,140
Nothing.

63
00:07:32,820 --> 00:07:34,260
You're not fond of

64
00:07:34,260 --> 00:07:35,620
Miss Ruoxi, are you?

65
00:07:35,980 --> 00:07:36,940
Don't talk nonsense.

66
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:39,900
Don't tarnish her good name.

67
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:42,340
So it is true then.

68
00:07:43,060 --> 00:07:44,660
I was just worried
about finding someone.

69
00:07:44,660 --> 00:07:45,540
You'll do.

70
00:07:48,260 --> 00:07:49,220
What is it?

71
00:07:51,060 --> 00:07:51,900
Nothing.

72
00:07:52,220 --> 00:07:53,100
Don't worry.

73
00:07:53,100 --> 00:07:54,220
I'll help you.

74
00:07:56,740 --> 00:07:58,020
Where are those two?

75
00:08:03,140 --> 00:08:03,940
Come here!

76
00:08:04,220 --> 00:08:05,060
Hurry up!

77
00:08:05,340 --> 00:08:06,140
Let's go.

78
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:12,500
Let me introduce you to two friends.

79
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:14,620
I met them both in the woods.

80
00:08:14,740 --> 00:08:16,180
This is Tu Jing.

81
00:08:16,940 --> 00:08:17,740
My savior.

82
00:08:18,340 --> 00:08:19,180
So it's you.

83
00:08:19,740 --> 00:08:20,980
You really do know each other.

84
00:08:21,220 --> 00:08:21,780
Yes.

85
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,220
He saved my life before.

86
00:08:23,420 --> 00:08:24,540
So he's my savior.

87
00:08:26,260 --> 00:08:27,380
Ruoxi said

88
00:08:27,820 --> 00:08:29,180
I owe my life to you this time.

89
00:08:30,780 --> 00:08:32,220
That makes us even.

90
00:08:32,580 --> 00:08:33,980
No need to call me "savior" anymore.

91
00:08:34,740 --> 00:08:35,860
Just call me Yaoyang.

92
00:08:39,940 --> 00:08:40,340
Do you

93
00:08:40,980 --> 00:08:41,940
have a cold?

94
00:08:43,340 --> 00:08:44,140
And this is...?

95
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:46,340
I'm not all that,

96
00:08:46,540 --> 00:08:48,100
but I come from ancient times.

97
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:49,540
I'm a one-of-a-kind...

98
00:08:49,780 --> 00:08:51,060
I can't think of anything else.

99
00:08:52,540 --> 00:08:53,500
Don't listen to his nonsense.

100
00:08:53,820 --> 00:08:55,780
He's just a bragging mushroom spirit.

101
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:57,780
He tried to trick me earlier.

102
00:08:58,020 --> 00:08:59,340
But I gave him a good beating

103
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:01,020
and almost made him into mushroom soup!

104
00:09:01,620 --> 00:09:02,580
He was messing with you?

105
00:09:03,220 --> 00:09:04,140
No, no.

106
00:09:04,140 --> 00:09:05,660
It was all a misunderstanding.

107
00:09:06,340 --> 00:09:07,140
A misunderstanding.

108
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:08,700
He's Yuxun.

109
00:09:09,140 --> 00:09:10,980
He's been gathering herbs

110
00:09:10,980 --> 00:09:12,220
to help you recover.

111
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:13,500
That's true.

112
00:09:13,980 --> 00:09:15,580
He's a really good cook.

113
00:09:16,220 --> 00:09:16,860
I

114
00:09:17,180 --> 00:09:18,500
want to keep them both here.

115
00:09:18,940 --> 00:09:19,820
Is that alright?

116
00:09:20,340 --> 00:09:22,020
I can cook.

117
00:09:22,220 --> 00:09:23,620
I can also prepare herbs.

118
00:09:24,220 --> 00:09:26,260
Anyway, I have nowhere else to go.

119
00:09:26,860 --> 00:09:27,420
Right?

120
00:09:28,580 --> 00:09:30,740
You're not fully recovered yet.

121
00:09:30,740 --> 00:09:32,220
Having us both stay means we can

122
00:09:32,220 --> 00:09:33,660
look out for each other.

123
00:09:40,940 --> 00:09:42,260
We can clear out

124
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:44,140
that storage room over there.

125
00:09:45,140 --> 00:09:45,900
But

126
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:47,660
this is the immortal realm.

127
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:49,540
You can't wander around,

128
00:09:50,980 --> 00:09:52,340
or the Immortal Venerable
might find out.

129
00:09:52,980 --> 00:09:53,660
Understood.

130
00:09:54,020 --> 00:09:54,660
Great!

131
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:32,240
♪What is flickering?♪

132
00:10:32,460 --> 00:10:34,980
♪Shining, delicate, and bright♪

133
00:10:35,140 --> 00:10:40,980
♪Like a trace of bitterness in a smile♪

134
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:43,860
♪What is falling?♪

135
00:10:44,300 --> 00:10:47,100
♪Clean, precise, and light♪

136
00:10:47,340 --> 00:10:52,540
♪Like enduring too many farewells♪

137
00:10:53,460 --> 00:10:55,060
♪When petals drift down♪

138
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:56,560
♪When the rain falls all around♪

139
00:10:56,660 --> 00:10:59,260
♪I gaze into your eyes♪

140
00:10:59,420 --> 00:11:01,120
♪Beyond the dunes♪

141
00:11:01,220 --> 00:11:02,500
♪No end in sight♪

142
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:05,500
♪I am like a mayfly♪

143
00:11:05,660 --> 00:11:07,060
♪I won't ask what the future holds♪

144
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,560
♪Nor will I run away♪

145
00:11:08,580 --> 00:11:11,520
♪Through all seasons by my side♪

146
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:16,780
♪Searching for sparks in the dust♪

147
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:33,840
♪What is flickering?♪

148
00:11:34,060 --> 00:11:36,540
♪Shining, delicate, and bright♪

149
00:11:36,740 --> 00:11:42,540
♪Like a trace of bitterness in a smile♪

150
00:11:42,980 --> 00:11:45,780
♪What is falling?♪

151
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:48,720
♪Clean, precise, and light♪

152
00:11:48,940 --> 00:11:53,940
♪Like enduring too many farewells♪

153
00:11:55,060 --> 00:11:56,540
♪When petals drift down♪

154
00:11:56,540 --> 00:11:58,040
♪When the rain falls all around♪

155
00:11:58,140 --> 00:12:00,700
♪I gaze into your eyes♪
